SIMPLE: wrathful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrathful
<hw>Wrath"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
wrath; very angry; greatly incensed; ireful; passionate; <as>as, a
wrathful man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Springing from, or expressing, wrath; <as>as, a
wrathful countenance</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wrathful</xex>
passions.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sprat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Furious; raging; indignant; resentful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wrath"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wrath"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrathily</ent>⟦br⟧
